Name: Eurozone 10-year Government Bond Yield
Periodicity:
Monthly From Jan 1970 To Dec 1985

Metadata: Notes: The data for 5-year bonds uses the average of 3-7 year bonds from 1989 to 1993, and the series for 10-year bonds uses the average of 7-15 year bonds from 1989 to 1993.  Data for benchmark, constant maturity bonds begin in June 1993. Data are the average yield for bonds issued by Eurozone member countries. Prior to 1999 the yields are an average of the yield of countries within the European Economic Community.
